   </svg>
  </copy-clipboard>
 </i18n-message></h2>
<p>There are multiple modes for deployment of <span style="--color: #333">RKE2 Kubernetes Distribution such as </span>Single-Node (Without HA), Multi-Node (Without HA) and High Availability installation. This guide enlists the pre-requisites for Single-Node (Without HA) and Multi-Node (Without HA) only.</p>
<p>The two RKE2 modes (Single and Multi) for deployment should be decided based on what level of availability is required. For this, nodes should be prepared according to the structure of the solution as given below:</p>
<div data-component="panel" role="note" data-appearance="error">
 <div class="panel-content">
  <p>The steps in this guide need to be completed before moving on to any of these modes:</p>
  <ul>
   <li>
    <p>RKE2 Single-Node Installation ( Without HA )</p>
   </li>
   <li>
    <p>RKE2 Multi-Node Installation ( Without HA )</p>
   </li>
  </ul>
 </div>
</div>
